== How solidity arises from luminosity

When you go to sleep, let's say there's a blank canvas---that's the wisdom of dharmatā---the white color you see there in the chart. So it's a blank canvas and awareness is like a prism, volumetric prism that's filled, imbued with this pure cognition that goes through the prism of thinking essentially. Like is awareness pure consciousness or is there a little veil there, a filter of some thought?

The thought that you could have, let's start with earth. Earth is associated with the klesha of pride. How is that, how is my pride making earth? Well, it's on a spectrum. On a coarse level, pride is, I'm better than you. But on a subtle lucid level, pride is Earth, it has the same tone to it. Solidity---I'm better than everybody, I know what I'm talking about, nobody else knows what they're talking about. Solidity, right? Earth.

Now remember, these are all asymmetrical and non-linear. They weave into each other. So you go to sleep and you start dreaming of a forest. Well, the ground, when you go to touch a tree and it feels solid, that's pride. It's just that we have an English word "pride" there that's a little reductive and things like that and has many connotations. But if you can expand your understanding of that word, you will start to see. 

And particularly when you start to soften out that coarse linguistic narrative, the one that's always talking, talking, talking, contemplating, contemplating, creating an electromagnetic psychic constraint, so you're only here in this dimension. You can feel it somatically in your brain, throughout your skull, in the center of your brain, throughout your neck and shoulders, stomach, pelvis, legs. You can feel it when you're locked into a smaller dimension. It's like a mood, a perspective, a predisposition, a state of consciousness.

So you go to sleep, you're dreaming of the earth, and let's say there's a little campfire there. That fire doesn't have solidity, it has heat, right? Can be utilized, can burn us, etc. Well, that's associated with desire. When that starts to soften, particularly because of the Tögal aspect helps a lot with the elements. That's why we hinge on the clear light so much---the presence.

Just noticing, all of you can do this right now: just notice presence within objects that you're seeing, hearing, etc. There's a pure presence. That's the wisdom of dharmatā permeating everything---the nature of mind, the nature of phenomenon.

So if you have a fire there, it's appearing as a fire---that's your dream language. But discernment---which is the counterpart to fire, is actually there. So just like with pride, have the wisdom of equality where earth is. So when you're walking on the earth, that feeling of separation and "I'm better"---or even on a lucid level, "I'm earth", that feeling is softening up and you have the wisdom of equality. And then with this wisdom of dharmatā---your awareness permeating everything, the fire is also revealing itself to be wisdom.

But we have these reductive English words, no offense to the English language, I mean it only has about 1.2 million words so it's not that versatile and that useful, right? So we have to accept our own limitations when we talk about these things.

So I'll stop here, but I just wanted to point out, because it's the second time you inquired about something very, very powerful here---because this is dealing with the reification of reality. And awareness needs to start to come into your dreams---just allow awareness to slowly come into your dreams, and your hypnagogic and hypnopompic states, your little bardos where you're going to sleep and you may notice some lucidity there and things like that.

Get to know your lucid mind. Stabilize into your lucid mind so it doesn't have to drive for you. You'll start to get into it and then your thoughts can spark off of that rather than us being in a different dimension than our lucidity, which is the fourth time: past, present and future.

So I didn't mean to neglect this other hand, I know your hand was up there, but he was inquiring about this and it's very fundamental to our approach. So I just wanted to share and entertain and start to open this up for you, that solidity---things like earth, air, fire, space, water. Now I know, these are just five, we're reducing everything, but to begin to see, or at least entertain the possibility of luminosity. Okay? And luminosity in the sense of just like when you go to sleep, you dream of a forest, that's all mind.

Let's say you're sitting here at a campfire in the forest and you're sitting cross-legged and you're enjoying the view and the smell, and all of sudden you take away all the colors. Now there's just pure luminosity, isn't there? There isn't even any subject and object because that was all cognition too.

Yeah, and when you explore this throughout different spiritualities and sciences and things like that, remember---mind, consciousness, awareness, these are all synonymous. And we can define consciousness---rather than leaving it mysterious and undefined---we can say "living intelligence." That's how I define it because you can find that in a single cell organism. You can find it in a box jellyfish that has no brain, no heart. You can find in atoms and light all over the place---we have living intelligence, even if the intelligence is irrelevant. You know, even if you're banging your head up against the wall, it's still a kind of intelligence.

Okay, so any questions about this stuff? Comments, anything? Yes, join on in there.

